00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:35,991
He is funny looking.
I would not mention it.

242
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,513
Of course not.

243
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:41,798
I figured you would not.
But sometimes, you know -

244
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:46,397
- things accidentally slip out
and then, you know...

245
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,991
Watch it on that stair.

246
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:56,072
Who designed these steps?
The Marquis de Sade?

247
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,231
Why is it so heavy? It is mostly air.

248
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,277
And glass, so be careful.

249
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:04,433
My aunt knitted one of these.
It was much lighter than this.

250
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:09,720
- This secret of yours relates to this?
- Sort of, yes.

251
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:14,874
What are you doing, Charlie?
I cannot hold this by myself!

252
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:19,313
You do not have to tell me.

253
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,038
Okay, I will tell you.

254
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:24,909
All right, start talking. Here we go.

255
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:30,352
I think I have discovered a comet.

256
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:36,790
It is no big deal,
there are a lot of comets.

257
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,996
I was working on this paper -

258
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:45,633
- on the ork cloud, and I discovered
a mathematical irregularity.

259
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:49,998
I have not climbed so many steps
since I went to the Maharishi.

260
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:57,349
I think it is a series of ten comets...
Watch it around this corner.

261
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:02,319
Or the forerunner of a big comet
which is due back this summer.

262
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:04,391
Will you find it with this?

263
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:08,109
No, my uncle is looking for it
in a big scope in Arizona.

264
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,032
I carried it up here for nothing?

265
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:14,955
Not really. Put that counter balance
on that arm with the key.

266
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:19,079
- So, what do you get if you are right?
- Nothing.

267
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:23,119
Well, I graduate, that is for sure...
And I get to name it.

268
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:26,636
That is pretty good. Sort of historical.

269
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:29,358
Comet Kowalski.

270
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:33,274
Why? You could give it a beautiful name.

271
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:36,557
- That is my name.
- It is? Roxanne Kowalski?

272
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,836
Oh, sorry.

273
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,070
So, when did you find out about this?

274
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:46,872
July 1 4, 22:08:31...
Give or take ten days.

275
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:52,558
- That would really be something.
- Yes.

276
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:03,269
Do not look now,
but the Viking just came in.

277
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:09,430
Come in, shake hands with the mayor.
You will look important.

278
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,192
He should be bronzed.

279
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:14,432
I am told you are
fast, efficient and brilliant -

280
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,795
- with the ladies.

281
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:22,316
If anything happens to you,
C.D. will be all over my Kazistkey...

282
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:46,916
- Get a hold of yourself.
- It is now or never.

283
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:51,873
- Do it, Roxanne.
- There is only one way to tell.

284
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:55,794
Okay, when he comes out -

285
00:24:55,960 --> 00:25:00,033
- I will invite him
to a Nelson tradition of hot-tubbing, -

286
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:05,115
- and I will set him up with some
mulled wine, and I will bathe him a lot.

287
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:08,636
- I am shocked.
- I am not shocked.

288
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:14,473
Confidence, confidence... A little
water and I am ready to talk to her.

289
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:17,630
Oh, no!

290
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:54,271
- Do you remember me?
- I am trying to put it behind me.

291
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:59,639
- Is this your shop?
- Yes, all mine.

292
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:03,588
- It is perfect.
- Thank you very much.

293
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:07,912
- It is really you.
- I appreciate that.

294
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:13,473
Come in and check out the freeze-dried
animals, they are incredibly lifelike.

295
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,596
Maybe next time.

296
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:35,119
C.D., it came to me
last night in a flash.

297
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:36,429
What is that?

298
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:41,037
The thing, the gimmick:
The Nelson promotional cow!

299
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,277
You give her a name:
Suzy, Bossy...

300
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:51,195
You put her picture in our posters,
teaching her to drink a beer.

301
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:55,035
- These things work.
- I think it is a fantastic idea.

302
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:58,988
- You like it?
- I love it, I think it is great!

303
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:04,837
I think it is brilliant, what an idea!
And I was there, I saw it happen:

304
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:10,154
He took the idea, ripe on the tree.
He plucked it and he put it in his pocket.

305
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:13,198
It is, dare I say, genius?

306
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:19,629
No, no... but maybe it is. Maybe I am
in the presence of greatness...

307
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,632
- Have you met C.D. yet?
- No, not yet.

308
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:29,271
- There is something you should know.
- He has a big nose, right?

309
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:35,230
- Whatever you do, do not stare.
- Come on, I will not stare.

310
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:40,713
None of us would, but you get there
and you feel yourself not staring.

311
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:44,759
Then it seems obvious
you are not staring, so you will look -

312
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:47,559
- and you will think, "I am staring."

313
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:54,193
You think, "this is ridiculous",
so you take a good look, and you think:

314
00:27:54,360 --> 00:28:00,276
"I am looking at a man who, when he
washes his face, loses the bar of soap."

315
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:04,999
- Thank you, guys.
- Do not say we did not warn you.

316
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:16,949
You think people go to Sun Valley
to see their fire department?

317
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:20,317
No, work with me.
You have to use promotion.

318
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:24,268
That way the town grows and
the fire department grows.

319
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:27,671
You cannot run a fire department
with the 7 banana brothers -

320
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:29,353
- you need professionals.

321
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:32,956
This town could be another Aspen.
They make tons of money.

322
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:37,989
As soon as this Oktoberfest is over,
you will get your funds back.

323
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:47,790
I have a drink, then I start to relax and
then I start to have fun.

324
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:51,794
It is not something I want to start
at this point in my life.

325
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,950
I heard you were tough.

326
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,435
I am...

327
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:02,152
But if you use a little tenderizer,
I might cook up pretty good.

328
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,072
Arsehole.

329
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,356
Where are you going, big nose?

330
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:13,351
Pardon me?

331
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:17,397
You heard me, <i>big nose.</i>

332
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,789
- Is that it?
- Yes.

333
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,748
You really got me on that one,
did you not?

334
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,678
Wait a second...

335
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,710
What a waste of an opportunity.

336
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:36,395
Someone is standing
in front of you with this -

337
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,074
- and all you can think up is
"big nose"?

338
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:41,674
Can you think up something better?

339
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:46,078
Yes, I think I can think up
something better. Come here.

340
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:51,513
With this dart... I will think up
whatever number you hit.

341
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,356
Twenty!

342
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,877
Two out of three.

343
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:07,795
- Twenty.
- Darts Champion, Denver, 1 987.

344
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:11,159
Come on, Charlie, you can do it.

345
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:14,952
All right, twenty something betters.

346
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,555
I start with the obvious:

347
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:21,872
Excuse me, is that your nose
or did a bus park on your face?

348
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:27,319
Meterological:
Everybody take cover, she will blow!

349
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:31,758
Fashionable: You could de-emphasise
your nose if you wore something larger -

350
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:34,115
- like Wyoming.

351
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:40,035
Personal: Well, here we are...
Just the three of us.

352
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:45,069
Punctual: Okay, your nose was on time,
but you were 15 minutes late.

353
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:48,789
Envious: Oh, I wish I were you -

354
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:53,078
- to be able to smell your own ear!

355
00:30:54,560 --> 00:31:00,476
Naughty: Some of the ladies have asked
if you would put that thing away.

356
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:04,394
Philosophical: It is not the size
of a nose that is important -

357
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:07,870
- it is what is in it that matters.

358
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:10,679
Humorous:
Laugh and the world laughs with you -

359
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:14,435
- sneeze and it is goodbye, Seattle.

360
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:20,630
Commercial: Hi, I am Earl Scheib
and I can paint that nose for $39.95!

361
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:23,189
Polite:
Would you mind not bobbing your head?

362
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:26,477
The orchestra keeps changing the tempo.

363
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,039
Melodic: Everybody.

364
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:33,069
<i>He has got the whole world in his nose.</i>

365
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:40,430
Sympathetic: What happened?
Did your parents lose a bet with God?

366
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:43,558
Complimentary:
You must love the birdies -

367
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:47,156
- to give them this to perch on.

368
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:52,599
Scientific: Say, does that thing there
influence the tides?

369
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:56,992
Obscure: Whoa,
I would hate to see the grindstone.

370
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,639
Well, think about it.

371
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:03,553
Inquiry:
When you stop and smell the flowers -

372
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:06,314
- are they afraid?

373
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:12,835
French: The pigs have refused
to find any more truffles -

374
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,719
- until you leave.

375
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:21,796
Pornographic: Finally a man
who can satisfy two women at once.

376
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:28,279
- How many is that?
- Fourteen, Chief.

377
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:32,194
All right, religious:
The Lord giveth -

378
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:35,557
- and He just kept on giving, did he not?

379
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,438
Fifteen.

380
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:44,270
Disgusting:
Say, who mows your nose hair?

381
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,271
Sixteen.

382
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:51,831
Paranoid:
Keep that guy away from my cocaine!

383
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,831
Seventeen.

384
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:58,596
Aromatic: It must be wonderful to wake
up in the morning and smell the coffee -

385
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:02,036
- in Brazil.
- Eighteen.

386
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:04,191
Appreciative: Oh, how original.

387
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:07,193
Most people just have their teeth capped.

388
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:09,351
Nineteen.

389
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,517
All right...

390
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:15,793
<i>You can do it, C.D., one more.</i>

391
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:22,315
Dirty:
Your name would not be Dick, would it?

392
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:26,710
You smartarse son of a bitch!

393
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:30,395
You flat-faced, flat-nosed flathead.

394
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:39,559
Has he fallen yet?

395
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:49,153
Did that copy of
"Being and Nothingness" by Jean Paul...

396
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:53,233
Jean Paul Sartre? Yes, it did.
I have it here, it is paid for.

397
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:58,394
- Great, thank you.
<i>- De rien... Il n'y a pas de quoi.</i>

398
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:01,552
- Okay.
- Do not mention it, bro.

399
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:08,478
"Therefore, my body is a conscious
structure of my consciousness."

400
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:13,350
Thank you, Chris. I was too embarrassed
to go and ask for it myself.

401
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:16,239
A little light reading, Andy?

402
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:20,313
I got $9,000 for the house this summer.

403
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:23,995
- Which one of the five?
- The one on Rush Street.

404
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:28,631
- You are soaking Roxanne for $9,000?
- I am not.

405
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:33,794
- You like her, do you not?
- What is there not to like?

406
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:37,509
- Why do you not ask her out?
- No, I cannot.

407
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:41,355
I have a 3 o'clock and a
5 o'clock, the women are lined up...

408
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:44,239
Mostly because of the old saying -

409
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:47,870
- about a man's nose relating to
the size of...

410
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:51,749
- The size of what?
- Come on, everybody knows this.

411
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:55,549
Hey, Sophie. Do you know the old saying
about a man's nose?

412
00:34:55,720 --> 00:35:00,794
You mean how the size of a man's nose
relates to the size of his...?

413
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:03,115
Oh, my God!

414
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:05,476
I love doing it to them.

415
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:10,270
- Your tea, sir... and picks.
- Thank you.

416
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:13,992
So, why do you not ask her out?

417
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:19,236
Sometimes I take a walk at night and
I see couples walking, holding hands -

418
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:22,551
- and I look at them and I think:
"Why not me?"

419
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:26,713
Then I catch my shadow on the wall...

420
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:31,671
- Why do you not get that nose job?
- I did.

421
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:35,636
It is the word: Rhinoplasty.
It is as unpleasant -

422
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,791
- as haemorrhoids.

423
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:41,236
Those two words you do not want
to get involved in.

424
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:47,191
What about cosmetics? Shading along the
sides, down the slope, a bit on the end?

425
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:52,512
- It really helps.
- No, not for me. I cannot wear make up.

426
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:55,672
You should have stayed last night.

427
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,673
You were great, we were impressed.

428
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:01,354
Roxanne went on and on about you.

429
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,839
She did?

430
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,551
I think she is falling in love,
but she does not know it yet.

431
00:36:11,120 --> 00:36:14,874
What does she mean,
"she thinks she is falling in love"?

432
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,713
It has been known to happen.

433
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:35,394
C.D., this is Chris McConnell.

434
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:40,634
It is a pleasure meeting you. I am sorry
we have been missing each other.

435
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:42,836
Are you all right?

436
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,356
I know you have met the guys...

437
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:49,548
How is your room?

438
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:07,398
It is hypnotic, is it not?

439
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:10,229
It is huge!

440
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:15,239
It is enormous, it is gigantic...

441
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:20,714
They said it was big,
but I did not expect it to be BIG.

442
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:31,469
Do you want to shoot some pool?
Rack them up, we will play a game.

443
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,389
You will not kill me? The guys said...

444
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:40,793
- Ordinarily I would, but not today.
- Why not?

445
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:47,115
Because yesterday she did not,
but today... she does.

446
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:59,998
You finally have a sense of humour
about your nose?

447
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:06,876
Rack them up.

448
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:13,108
Okay, turn on the hose. The secret to
moving a hose is in the rhythm.

449
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:18,718
To the left:
One and two and three.

450
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:22,919
To the right:
One and two and three.

451
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:25,275
Now forward.

452
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:29,755
Now back.

453
00:38:31,600 --> 00:38:34,194
I cannot stand this.

454
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:52,589
Turn it off! What are you doing?

455
00:39:04,280 --> 00:39:05,952
Turn it off! Turn it off!

456
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:09,556
Get a good stream.
Lean into it, trust it.

457
00:39:09,720 --> 00:39:12,280
Remember: Water is your friend.

458
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:16,233
What is our signal
for charging the hose?

459
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:20,552
Remember, it is like Big Bird...
like on "Sesame Street".

460
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:43,479
No, not him again.

461
00:39:44,200 --> 00:39:48,193
There he is...
Back up a second.

462
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:51,676
Flirting with Sophie and Lydia again.

463
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:54,559
Charlie, can I talk to you?

464
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,870
Well...

465
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:01,475
All right.

466
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:11,310
Okay, was I right?

467
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:15,871
- Yes, it is ugly.
- It really is.

468
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:23,675
- What I will say is a little forward...
- Good.

469
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:29,029
There is someone I think
I should get to know better.

470
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:31,509
Someone who I think likes me too.

471
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:34,353
- You know what I mean?
- Yes.

472
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:36,829
I think he wants to talk to me.

473
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:41,516
I can see him trying, but he will not.
I like him for that.

474
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:45,798
Maybe this guy needs you
to make the first move.

475
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:48,520
That is why I am talking to you.

476
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:53,631
So... what do you know about this guy?

477
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:56,268
I know he is interesting...

478
00:40:57,640 --> 00:41:00,154
- Different.
- Yes.

479
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:04,359
Intelligent.
Handsome.

480
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:08,638
- He is what?
- He is handsome.

481
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:14,193
Is it not amazing? If you have feelings
for someone, you see them as handsome?

482
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:18,672
- Everyone thinks he is.
- No, not everyone, believe me.

483
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:21,513
What are you talking about?

484
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:26,791
Nothing.
It is great that he is all these things.

485
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:31,670
I have only seen him a few times.
We have never even spoken -

486
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:35,150
- we just exchanged
some goofy looks.

487
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:40,519
- Why are you telling me this?
- He works for you. Chris McConnell.

488
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:46,475
What is he like? No, do not tell me.
I will let it unfold.

489
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:51,871
Since you are working with him,
maybe you could encourage him.

490
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:55,953
He may not say anything all summer
and then I will be gone.

491
00:41:56,120 --> 00:42:00,238
- If it comes up.
- C.D., thank you.

492
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:03,311
I know I am forward.

493
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:07,958
You were really great the other night.

494
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:10,714
It is the first time
I have seen anyone be brave.

495
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:13,553
I have been a lot braver since then.

496
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:21,837
This time I want you to do it.
Cut it off!

497
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:25,356
I am tired of having a magnificent,
fabulous, interesting nose.

498
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:28,876
I want a cute,
petite, little button nose.

499
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:33,431
- Give me the American beauty.
- C.D., you know I cannot.

500
00:42:33,600 --> 00:42:37,070
Yes you can, get the knife. Cut it, Dave.

501
00:42:37,240 --> 00:42:43,475
I cannot. Allergies to anesthetics are
dangerous; you will go into a coma.

502
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:47,155
We will do it the old-fashioned way.

503
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:50,595
Do not be stupid.

504
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:55,515
- I want to look like Diana Ross.
- What you want is psychotherapy.

505
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:59,878
I can hear it now:
"Get used to it. $85, please."

506
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:06,157
Have you ever thought you
were born with this nose for a reason?

507
00:43:06,320 --> 00:43:08,231
Oh yes -

508
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:11,790
- like opening coke bottles.

509
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:24,712
Can I look at those nose cards
one more time?

510
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,996
Yes, sure.

511
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:54,598
Hello darling,
I have not seen you in a while.

512
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:59,510
She is so beautiful,
I saw her in that bar...

513
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:03,229
- She is interesting, too.
- Yes, did you see her legs?

514
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:05,231
She also has a sense of humour.

515
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:10,997
She wants to meet me? I cannot
believe this; God, my third day here...

516
00:44:11,160 --> 00:44:13,310
She is smart, too. Astrology...

517
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,710
- Astronomy.
- Yes, right.

518
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:17,871
God, we will meet, really?

519
00:44:19,120 --> 00:44:21,395
So what do I do?

520
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:24,516
How do I meet her?

521
00:44:24,680 --> 00:44:27,956
How about you walk up to her
and say hello?

522
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:31,590
No, then I would have to talk to her.

523
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,830
What are you talking about?

524
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:40,393
Around you guys I can relax and be
myself... I am funny, you know that.

525
00:44:40,560 --> 00:44:46,112
But around women I get a little...
It is not that I do not like them.

526
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:48,589
I just get a little nervous.

527
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:51,558
Okay,
get her telephone number and call her.

528
00:44:51,720 --> 00:44:54,792
Pass. Then I would have to talk to her.

529
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:56,837
I wanted to talk to her really bad -

530
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:01,710
- but I did not, because that is how
I would have talked to her: bad.

531
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:07,830
So every time you meet a woman
with charm and style and legs, -

532
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,719
- you will turn around and run.

533
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:14,236
That is a great idea. It is brilliant.

534
00:45:16,120 --> 00:45:18,270
It is a dumb game; why do we play it?

535
00:45:18,440 --> 00:45:21,671
- Tough game?
- We are on our way there.

536
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:27,399
- Do you know what "carpe diem" is?
- Some kind of fish, fish bait?

537
00:45:27,560 --> 00:45:31,439
No, it is Latin.
It means, "seize the day".

538
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:33,750
There may be no tomorrow, so do it now.

539
00:45:33,920 --> 00:45:36,753
Seek life now, while you have the chance.

540
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:41,152
- You think I should go after Roxannne?
- No, I would not. I would wait.

541
00:45:41,320 --> 00:45:43,311
Mail her a letter.

542
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:48,715
Okay, light the thing, see how you do.

543
00:45:57,760 --> 00:46:00,320
<i>C.D., come here. I have got it!</i>

544
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:11,118
You have got it all right.

545
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:14,352
How to talk to Roxanne.
I will take a chance.

546
00:46:14,520 --> 00:46:18,354
The girl likes me, what am I afraid of?
She is no rocket scientist.

547
00:46:18,520 --> 00:46:21,512
Actually, she is a rocket scientist.

548
00:46:21,680 --> 00:46:26,674
But of all the guys she likes me, right?
So what am I afraid of? Nothing.

549
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:30,628
I will do as you said...
I will write her a letter.

550
00:46:30,800 --> 00:46:34,190
I have a way with words.
I always crack the guys up.

551
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:38,273
This way I can plan what to say.
I can craft it.

552
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:42,274
In a letter I can be...
effer-goddamn-vescent.

553
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:49,596
- We cannot get it started.
- I will be out in a minute.

554
00:46:51,720 --> 00:46:55,998
- Andy, your coat is on fire.
- Yeah, right.

555
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:58,316
So what do you think?

556
00:46:58,480 --> 00:47:01,790
- What?!
- He is on fire, get his coat!

557
00:47:01,960 --> 00:47:04,155
No! Not the gasoline!

558
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:09,033
Can I help you?

559
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:14,479
Yes, I have a friend who is looking for
a cosmetic, if one exits -

560
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:21,193
- a sort of a shading arrangement.
Do you have anything in the shading area?

561
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:27,196
We have lots of blushers and things...
What specifically is it for?

562
00:47:27,360 --> 00:47:33,196
She has this feature that she would
like to... de-emphasise.

563
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:40,116
I see, she has this extra large feature
and she wants to make it look smaller?

564
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:43,470
I think a dark contour would be fine.

565
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:49,875
Great. How would she go about...
applying this thing?

566
00:47:52,760 --> 00:48:00,030
She would... just shade the area of the
feature to make it look...

567
00:48:00,640 --> 00:48:06,317
It would appear to be more shadows
and less actual... acreage.

568
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:09,916
- I mean area.
- I will take it.

569
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:13,197
- I will get a fresh one from the back.
- Thank you.

570
00:48:16,920 --> 00:48:19,434
I talked to Chris for you.

571
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:22,870
Great.

572
00:48:23,040 --> 00:48:25,110
Do you think he will call me?

573
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:27,589
He wants to write you a letter.

574
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:34,116
A letter? Is that not usually
at the end of a relationship?

575
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:39,229
No, it is really romantic, actually.
I will explain it to you outside.

576
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:42,039
C.D., here is your blush.

577
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:46,318
- Could you giftwrap that for me?
- Okay.

578
00:48:46,480 --> 00:48:49,517
These items I decided against.

579
00:48:53,080 --> 00:48:57,073
- Do you have a girlfriend?
- No, it is for my sister.

580
00:48:57,240 --> 00:49:02,109
- You have a sister?
- No, it is for my sister's girlfriend.

581
00:49:27,040 --> 00:49:30,271
Hi, Chris.
No, I am not doing anything.

582
00:49:30,440 --> 00:49:33,557
Just baking some eggs.

583
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,072
Sure, come on over. Bye.

584
00:49:39,480 --> 00:49:42,074
You should read the letter
before I send it.

585
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:45,073
Great, we will take a look at it.

586
00:49:47,560 --> 00:49:50,916
- It is quite an operation you have.
- Thank you.

587
00:49:56,360 --> 00:50:01,229
- Let us take a look at that letter.
- I think it is really good.

588
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:05,993
"Dear Roxanne, how is it going?
Do you want to have a drink sometime?

589
00:50:06,160 --> 00:50:08,833
If you do, check this box."

590
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:16,837
- How long did you work on this?
- Today. Since noon.

591
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:23,279
Chris, that is a very long time.
You cannot send her this.

592
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:24,839
What do you mean?

593
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:28,310
I like the concept,
but it has to be more interesting.

594
00:50:28,480 --> 00:50:29,993
I worked hard on that!

595
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:35,075
Take a pen, sit down and let me ask you
a question: how do you feel about her?

596
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:40,155
- Me, about her?
- How did you feel when you first saw her?

597
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:41,958
Horny.

598
00:50:43,120 --> 00:50:47,318
Okay, you cannot say you felt horny,
you have to change it.

599
00:50:47,480 --> 00:50:50,950
You have to say, " I felt... moved, -

600
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:56,109
- alive... on fire."

601
00:50:56,480 --> 00:50:57,913
That is beautiful.

602
00:50:58,080 --> 00:51:01,390
How did you feel
when you first spoke to her?

603
00:51:01,560 --> 00:51:03,551
Like a dickhead.

604
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:06,314
No, you cannot write that.

605
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:12,669
You have to say, "I felt like a child
standing in the sun for the first time -

606
00:51:12,840 --> 00:51:16,116
- feeling only your radiance."

607
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:20,831
"Radiance"; I like that.
I will underline that.

608
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:23,878
What did you do after you saw her?

609
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:27,633
I puked.

610
00:51:30,680 --> 00:51:35,629
After seeing you...
my only nourishment was you.

611
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:40,076
- C.D., you write the letter.
- No, you do it.

612
00:51:40,240 --> 00:51:44,472
You know how to say what I feel.
You write it and I will sign it.

613
00:51:44,640 --> 00:51:50,237
No, no, that is... dangerous.
That is lying.

614
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,630
Not if you write what I feel.

615
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:56,713
I sign my name and you write
what you imagine I am feeling.

616
00:51:56,880 --> 00:52:00,714
- It will work.
- What I imagine you are feeling?

617
00:52:00,880 --> 00:52:02,791
It is half-written already.

618
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:06,077
You have to change that poetic baloney.

619
00:52:06,240 --> 00:52:07,958
This is beautiful.

620
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:11,829
No, for Roxanne
you need something startling -

621
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:18,394
- something so strange it would
make her incapable of being reasonable.

622
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:21,870
- Can you do it?
- It is an challenge.

623
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,956
Get your favourite pen.

624
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:26,475
These are good.

625
00:52:26,640 --> 00:52:31,634
And some good quality paper
that really takes the ink.

626
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:34,678
- Oh, the food!
- I will take care of it.

627
00:52:34,840 --> 00:52:37,229
You just take your time.

628
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:02,595
Come on, boys, line up.

629
00:53:12,520 --> 00:53:16,638
- Six and a half minutes, not bad.
- Let us get into our gear.

630
00:53:24,400 --> 00:53:26,630
Let us go, boys.
It is Operation Snowball.

631
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:28,313
Snowball!

632
00:53:33,600 --> 00:53:36,478
Take the truck!

633
00:53:52,320 --> 00:53:54,675
Snowball, come on.

634
00:54:45,560 --> 00:54:50,315
Hi, how are you doing, Chief?
All is well that ends well.

635
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:58,914
Boys, the ladder is up. Boys!

636
00:55:00,040 --> 00:55:02,793
Wait, boys. The ladder is up!

637
00:55:24,240 --> 00:55:28,518
Let me show you a double binary,
just focus with this.

638
00:55:29,520 --> 00:55:32,159
You will see it, I am on a schedule.

639
00:55:33,920 --> 00:55:35,990
Roxanne, what is a light year?

640
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:39,675
Same as a regular year,
it just has less calories.

641
00:55:42,400 --> 00:55:43,628
What is it?

642
00:55:43,800 --> 00:55:46,951
It is two pairs of stars
revolving around each other, -

643
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:50,271
- but so far away
they look like one.

644
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:54,513
- What keeps them together?
- Mutual attraction.

645
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:57,513
That is fairly romantic.

646
00:55:58,680 --> 00:56:02,559
"Strange attractors
in my window of possible movement."

647
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:04,312
Say again?

648
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:07,438
"Passionate kisses
I hope you will read with your lips."

649
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:10,068
- Roxanne?
- Sorry.

650
00:56:11,080 --> 00:56:13,833
It is something from a letter I got...

651
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:16,831
An amazing letter.

652
00:56:17,000 --> 00:56:21,551
- You liked it?
- No, I did not like it. I loved it.

653
00:56:23,120 --> 00:56:25,076
- Whose letter?
- Chris.

654
00:56:25,240 --> 00:56:28,198
- He can write?
- I am melting.

655
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:32,791
Let me show you that dumbbell nebula.

656
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:37,590
There is something I do not get...

657
00:56:37,760 --> 00:56:42,515
The guy dodges me for days, so I think,
"Okay, he is not interested."

658
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:44,511
C.D. tells me of the letter -

659
00:56:44,680 --> 00:56:48,195
- so I figure it is about
why he will not talk to me.

660
00:56:48,360 --> 00:56:50,112
But it is not.

661
00:56:50,280 --> 00:56:53,795
It was strange and... intelligent -

662
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:55,757
- and sexual.

663
00:56:56,720 --> 00:57:01,555
Why is he writing?
He only lives a block and a half away.

664
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,556
Charlie?

665
00:57:06,240 --> 00:57:09,550
Do you want me
to ask him out for you?

666
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:13,676
She wants a date?

667
00:57:14,640 --> 00:57:17,234
C.D., it is all because of you.

668
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:29,034
Hey, what is the matter?

669
00:57:30,200 --> 00:57:34,352
She wants to see me tonight?
I cannot see her tonight.

670
00:57:34,520 --> 00:57:36,636
I am already a wreck.

671
00:57:36,800 --> 00:57:38,836
Relax.

672
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:42,834
You have to help me.
If I talk to her, I will die.

673
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:46,515
Here is what we do:
I give you something to memorise.

674
00:57:46,680 --> 00:57:50,195
- I cannot memorise.
- Anyone can memorise.

675
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:53,909
Say the Pledge of Allegiance.
You memorised that, right?

676
00:57:54,080 --> 00:57:59,791
Okay, I said,
"I pledge allegiance to the flag of..."

677
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:04,317
...which country, I do not know.

678
00:58:04,480 --> 00:58:06,710
We will think of something.

679
00:58:19,520 --> 00:58:23,672
- No letter this time, just face to face.
- Yes.

680
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:29,954
- Do you want to sit outside?
- Do I want to sit outside? Yes.

681
00:58:30,120 --> 00:58:33,954
- Here?
- Here on the porch, yes.

682
00:58:35,920 --> 00:58:39,515
- We can sit right here.
- Great.

683
00:58:43,720 --> 00:58:50,068
- It is a lovely evening.
- Oh, yes... It is an exquisite evening.

684
00:58:51,080 --> 00:58:58,236
Filled with... mysterious portents.
Magic and romance.

685
00:59:01,520 --> 00:59:06,275
- Why are you wearing that hat?
- Why? ...Because...

686
00:59:07,280 --> 00:59:09,271
Do not panic, stay calm.

687
00:59:12,600 --> 00:59:16,513
Because tonight... I am a hunter.

688
00:59:16,680 --> 00:59:22,198
Because tonight... I am a hunter.
Hunting for words.

689
00:59:23,120 --> 00:59:24,838
That is good, it is okay.

690
00:59:25,000 --> 00:59:26,956
Am I your prey?

691
00:59:27,440 --> 00:59:30,238
Yes, but not a defenceless one.

692
00:59:31,480 --> 00:59:35,189
Yes... but not a defenceless one.

693
00:59:36,120 --> 00:59:40,398
Not a rabbit.
You are a lioness.

694
00:59:43,560 --> 00:59:45,551
Alert and sensitive...

695
00:59:45,720 --> 00:59:49,998
Alert and sensitive to every mis-step.

696
00:59:53,040 --> 00:59:54,917
Move a little closer to her.

697
00:59:55,880 --> 01:00:01,352
Therefore I must move silently,
moving in towards you.

698
01:00:02,200 --> 01:00:03,918
Reach out your hand.

699
01:00:04,680 --> 01:00:10,789
I hand out... reaching to...
Car three, proceed to the 279.

700
01:00:11,080 --> 01:00:12,479
What?

701
01:00:13,160 --> 01:00:16,197
<i>Confirm, car three, confirm.</i>

702
01:00:16,360 --> 01:00:17,679
Confirm what?

703
01:00:19,280 --> 01:00:22,590
Confirm my feelings.

704
01:00:22,760 --> 01:00:26,309
- Confirm my feelings.
- Yes.

705
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:35,713
Because there is a heart here...
that wants yours to know -

706
01:00:35,920 --> 01:00:38,593
- there is a possible 502 on Main.

707
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:41,789
<i>Proceed to Main, confirm.</i>

708
01:00:51,560 --> 01:00:54,313
Are you not a hunter anymore?

709
01:00:54,480 --> 01:00:58,758
Not a hunter? No, I mean...

710
01:01:00,480 --> 01:01:04,268
It is really nice out, is it not?

711
01:01:04,640 --> 01:01:08,713
It is really, really...
what is the word I am looking for?

712
01:01:08,880 --> 01:01:12,350
Nice, yes, that is it.

713
01:01:13,480 --> 01:01:16,233
So, now you are the weatherman?

714
01:01:21,640 --> 01:01:24,996
I loved your letter.
It was beautiful.

715
01:01:25,160 --> 01:01:27,674
Where did you learn to write like that?

716
01:01:27,840 --> 01:01:32,550
