757
01:04:31,080 --> 01:04:33,913
I was... happy? dizzy?

758
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:36,478
Thirsty?

759
01:04:37,400 --> 01:04:40,392
This is stupid.
Stupid!

760
01:04:40,560 --> 01:04:43,552
I was stupid and I was also...

761
01:04:44,560 --> 01:04:47,154
Tripping? ...bumbling.

762
01:04:49,120 --> 01:04:52,795
I was a stupid, bumbling... pointer.

763
01:04:53,880 --> 01:04:54,995
Pointer?

764
01:04:55,240 --> 01:04:58,277
No, no... stupid ass.

765
01:05:00,680 --> 01:05:03,319
So why did you say those things?

766
01:05:04,560 --> 01:05:06,994
Tell her you were afraid.

767
01:05:07,160 --> 01:05:11,915
- Because I was afraid.
- Of me? Afraid of what?

768
01:05:12,080 --> 01:05:14,389
Tell her you were afraid of words.

769
01:05:14,560 --> 01:05:16,869
- What?
- Words.

770
01:05:17,040 --> 01:05:19,838
Because I was afraid of worms, Roxanne!

771
01:05:21,520 --> 01:05:23,476
Worms!?

772
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:26,195
What are you saying to me?

773
01:05:28,560 --> 01:05:32,519
When I said "worms"
I meant "words", Roxanne.

774
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:34,272
Give me your coat.

775
01:05:34,440 --> 01:05:40,276
Words are all used up, they are hard
to say, they have all been wasted -

776
01:05:40,440 --> 01:05:45,468
- on the shampoo commercials
and the ads and the flavourings.

777
01:05:45,640 --> 01:05:50,919
Hollow, beautiful words.
How can you love a floor wax?

778
01:05:51,080 --> 01:05:52,752
How can you love a diaper?

779
01:05:52,920 --> 01:05:57,789
How can I use the same word about you
that is used about a stuffing?

780
01:05:57,960 --> 01:06:01,077
I am exploding with love,
but cannot use the word.

781
01:06:01,240 --> 01:06:02,958
