955
01:21:48,880 --> 01:21:51,394
I have to tell him about the letters.

956
01:22:31,680 --> 01:22:33,511
Coming.

957
01:22:35,880 --> 01:22:37,996
Just a second, I will be right back.

958
01:22:49,320 --> 01:22:50,958
What are you doing here?

959
01:22:51,120 --> 01:22:53,156
There was no one there.

960
01:22:54,160 --> 01:22:57,038
- What?
- There was no one there.

961
01:23:06,760 --> 01:23:08,955
What is going on?

962
01:23:09,120 --> 01:23:11,270
I will get it.

963
01:23:34,440 --> 01:23:38,149
Probably just kids...
Damn kids nowadays.

964
01:23:42,880 --> 01:23:45,872
- Guess why I came back early?
- The door again.

965
01:23:46,040 --> 01:23:48,793
There was no doorbell.

966
01:23:48,960 --> 01:23:51,076
There it was again, I heard it.

967
01:23:51,240 --> 01:23:54,118
Probably some kids. I will get it now.

968
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:57,875
- There was no doorbell.
- I will take care of it.

969
01:24:07,600 --> 01:24:09,591
There it was again.

970
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:12,877
She might mention some letters.

971
01:24:13,040 --> 01:24:15,395
You wrote her a few letters.

972
01:24:15,560 --> 01:24:18,028
- How many?
- Three a day.

973
01:24:18,200 --> 01:24:20,839
Six days, six times three is eighteen!

974
01:24:21,000 --> 01:24:23,070
Well, twenty.

975
01:24:23,240 --> 01:24:25,117
Twenty or so...

976
01:24:31,160 --> 01:24:33,276
Nobody there.

977
01:24:35,200 --> 01:24:39,716
Chris... do you know why
I came back early?

978
01:24:39,880 --> 01:24:43,555
Every day, every hour
you sent me something new.

979
01:24:43,720 --> 01:24:46,792
I could not stand it. I had to see you.

980
01:24:46,960 --> 01:24:50,270
It was just letters...
Twenty or so.

981
01:24:50,440 --> 01:24:53,989
- Think of what you wrote.
- I am trying.

982
01:24:55,680 --> 01:24:59,195
- Wait... I want to know the real you.
- No!

983
01:24:59,360 --> 01:25:01,555
The one I spoke to at the window.

984
01:25:01,720 --> 01:25:04,314
This is the real me, good old Chris.

985
01:25:04,480 --> 01:25:08,951
I like hanging out,
lifting weights; I am into my body.

986
01:25:09,120 --> 01:25:11,395
You do not have to do that with me.

987
01:25:11,560 --> 01:25:14,711
I know you and love you
from your letters.

988
01:25:14,880 --> 01:25:17,075
Is it not enough I am cute?

989
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:21,634
Do you not see,
it would not matter if you were ugly.

990
01:25:21,800 --> 01:25:23,358
No!

991
01:25:23,520 --> 01:25:27,308
- Teach me what you know.
- I can play the guitar a little.

992
01:25:27,480 --> 01:25:30,040
- We could travel.
- No, I hate pasta.

993
01:25:30,200 --> 01:25:34,193
- I want to go to concerts with you.
- We could... boogie, or what?

994
01:25:34,360 --> 01:25:37,432
- We can just talk, Chris.
- Talk?

995
01:25:37,600 --> 01:25:39,636
Roxanne, I -

996
01:25:40,680 --> 01:25:42,830
- am feeling a little...

997
01:25:43,000 --> 01:25:45,719
I am not feeling well, I have to go.

998
01:26:19,160 --> 01:26:21,754
So? Are you coming or not?

999
01:26:23,200 --> 01:26:24,997
Yes.

1000
01:26:28,400 --> 01:26:31,790
- Will you tell her?
- I cannot.

1001
01:26:33,000 --> 01:26:37,357
Chris, you have to tell her,
it is not nice.

1002
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:42,198
Do you have any paper?
I could write her.

1003
01:26:42,360 --> 01:26:44,715
I have experience at that.

1004
01:26:44,880 --> 01:26:48,873
I have some in my glove compartment.
I will get it.

1005
01:26:55,760 --> 01:27:01,596
Roxanne called. She sounded really weird,
she wants you to come over right away.

1006
01:27:03,400 --> 01:27:07,791
- Jerry, it is a re-match.
- He owes me 50 bucks.

1007
01:27:16,680 --> 01:27:18,477
Come in.

1008
01:27:25,360 --> 01:27:28,636
- What is it?
- Read this.

1009
01:27:32,240 --> 01:27:37,189
"Dear Roxanne. I have met someone else,
and she is real cute, too.

1010
01:27:37,360 --> 01:27:41,069
I hope I have not hurt you,
but I probably did.

1011
01:27:41,240 --> 01:27:46,360
It was really nice knowing you,
and now I am going to be a dealer in Tahoe.

1012
01:27:46,520 --> 01:27:48,715
Yours truly -

1013
01:27:48,880 --> 01:27:52,350
- t-r-u-l-e-y, Chris."

1014
01:27:54,840 --> 01:27:58,958
Then I found this along with it
under the door.

1015
01:28:05,480 --> 01:28:08,790
Read it... read it out loud.

1016
01:28:11,800 --> 01:28:14,997
"All day long I think,

1017
01:28:16,000 --> 01:28:20,312
'Where is she, what is she doing now?"

1018
01:28:21,240 --> 01:28:27,998
Occasionally, I see you on the street
and I feel the nerves in my stomach -

1019
01:28:28,160 --> 01:28:30,958
- a wave crashing over me."

1020
01:28:32,000 --> 01:28:35,470
- It is so him.
- Go on.

1021
01:28:36,720 --> 01:28:40,030
"I remember everything about you; -

1022
01:28:40,200 --> 01:28:45,228
- every move
no matter how insignificant it may seem.

1023
01:28:45,400 --> 01:28:49,234
July 1 1, 2:30 in the afternoon.

1024
01:28:51,080 --> 01:28:57,269
You changed your hair...
not that much, but I noticed.

1025
01:28:58,400 --> 01:29:02,518
It was as though
I had looked at the sun too long.

1026
01:29:02,680 --> 01:29:07,834
I could close my eyes
and see it again and again.

1027
01:29:08,520 --> 01:29:14,789
The way your hair moved, your walk,
your dress, everywhere I looked."

1028
01:29:20,120 --> 01:29:22,714
It is nice, is it not?

1029
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:26,472
It has a... I feel...

1030
01:29:26,640 --> 01:29:30,918
- Finish it.
- I did, it just runs out.

1031
01:29:31,080 --> 01:29:33,674
You have to turn it over.

1032
01:29:35,680 --> 01:29:40,470
"C.D. wrote this. Call me.
Dixie."

1033
01:29:43,080 --> 01:29:48,279
I went through all of the other letters.
They are all in the same hand.

1034
01:29:48,440 --> 01:29:53,195
It was your voice under the balcony.
Chris did not write the letters, you did.

1035
01:29:56,680 --> 01:29:58,750
Yes.

1036
01:30:00,080 --> 01:30:06,315
All this time right there in front of me,
and I could not even see you.

1037
01:30:07,320 --> 01:30:11,279
You bastard!
How could you trick me like that?

1038
01:30:11,440 --> 01:30:13,351
I tried to make you feel good.

1039
01:30:13,520 --> 01:30:16,637
- You played with me.
- You should have guessed it.

1040
01:30:16,800 --> 01:30:21,078
- So, it is my fault?
- The signatures do not match the letters.

1041
01:30:21,240 --> 01:30:23,993
You do not check that in a love letter.

1042
01:30:24,160 --> 01:30:27,072
Because you wanted to believe it.

1043
01:30:27,240 --> 01:30:31,711
All the romance wrapped up
in a cute nose and a cute arse.

1044
01:30:31,880 --> 01:30:33,996
You even got me in bed!

1045
01:30:34,160 --> 01:30:38,711
- Yes, on your first date!
- Only because <i>you</i> seduced me.

1046
01:30:38,880 --> 01:30:43,158
You went to bed with him too fast.
One frilly word and you are horizontal.

1047
01:30:43,320 --> 01:30:46,437
I do not think
I went to bed with <i>him.</i>

1048
01:30:46,600 --> 01:30:50,479
Somebody was up there,
it sure was not me.

1049
01:30:50,640 --> 01:30:53,916
Then who?
Chris could not have seduced me.

1050
01:30:54,080 --> 01:30:58,437
- That is just what I told Dixie.
- You told Dixie?

1051
01:30:58,600 --> 01:31:01,239
I just mentioned it, I did not mean to...

1052
01:31:01,400 --> 01:31:03,834
You son of a bitch! You bastard!

1053
01:31:04,000 --> 01:31:05,797
How could you lie?

1054
01:31:05,960 --> 01:31:09,077
I tried to tell you
how I felt about you.

1055
01:31:09,240 --> 01:31:12,198
It was a lousy way of telling me!

1056
01:31:12,360 --> 01:31:14,271
Just get out!

1057
01:31:15,280 --> 01:31:17,316
Wait a second, I am out. Get in!

1058
01:31:17,480 --> 01:31:20,040
- No, get out!
- Get in!

1059
01:31:20,200 --> 01:31:23,590
- Get off this porch.
- Fine.

1060
01:31:26,240 --> 01:31:28,629
Do not try throwing my hat at me.

1061
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:35,988
Guess what the rest of the letter said?
It said, "P.S. I was only kidding."

1062
01:31:36,680 --> 01:31:41,470
- Ten more seconds and I am leaving.
- What did you say?

1063
01:31:41,640 --> 01:31:44,552
Ten more seconds and I am leaving.

1064
01:31:44,720 --> 01:31:49,555
- What did you think I said?
- Earn more sessions by sleeving.

1065
01:31:51,240 --> 01:31:56,473
- What the hell does that mean?
- I do not know, that is why I came out.

1066
01:31:59,800 --> 01:32:01,438
Ten...

1067
01:32:01,880 --> 01:32:03,393
Nine...

1068
01:32:04,160 --> 01:32:05,752
Eight...

1069
01:32:06,320 --> 01:32:07,753
Seven...

1070
01:32:38,560 --> 01:32:41,711
Chris came and took all his stuff.

1071
01:33:04,920 --> 01:33:07,673
There is a fire somewhere.

1072
01:33:08,640 --> 01:33:10,870
Get into gear.

1073
01:33:58,840 --> 01:34:01,593
That is where I put Bossy.

1074
01:34:05,600 --> 01:34:07,875
We have got a burner, boys.

1075
01:34:09,400 --> 01:34:12,790
Two 2 1 /2 inch lines
from the pump to the fire.

1076
01:34:12,960 --> 01:34:16,635
Three 1 1/2 inch lines
from the hydrant to the pump.

1077
01:34:16,800 --> 01:34:19,075
If it gets to the station,
the whole town goes.

1078
01:34:30,800 --> 01:34:35,191
I want a water curtain with
a full fog pattern on both exposures.

1079
01:34:46,640 --> 01:34:48,790
One, two, three...

1080
01:34:52,960 --> 01:34:54,712
We are doing it, C.D.!

1081
01:34:59,480 --> 01:35:01,550
Take it easy, here we go.

1082
01:35:03,440 --> 01:35:05,635
Come on, Bossy. Let us go, boy.

1083
01:35:11,280 --> 01:35:14,192
You are all
real goddamn fire fighters now.

1084
01:35:15,200 --> 01:35:17,760
To all us real goddamn fire fighters.

1085
01:35:18,760 --> 01:35:21,115
Thanks to us, no one got fried.

1086
01:35:21,280 --> 01:35:24,352
We beat this fire by a nose.

1087
01:35:28,040 --> 01:35:30,634
Well said.

1088
01:35:34,240 --> 01:35:36,708
I want to see you.

1089
01:35:38,160 --> 01:35:40,310
A toast.

1090
01:35:41,320 --> 01:35:47,350
I would like to say that I would
rather be with the people of this town -

1091
01:35:48,680 --> 01:35:51,911
- than with the finest people
in the world.

1092
01:36:20,040 --> 01:36:22,429
What are friends for?

1093
01:36:58,520 --> 01:37:02,798
When I close my eyes
I see you again and again.

1094
01:37:02,960 --> 01:37:08,159
Your eyes, your face...
the way you walk.

1095
01:37:09,200 --> 01:37:12,829
Your style, your wit...

1096
01:37:14,320 --> 01:37:16,880
And your nose, Charlie.

1097
01:37:18,560 --> 01:37:21,154
It does not quite work, does it?

1098
01:37:22,800 --> 01:37:27,351
I went inside and thought about
why I was attracted to Chris.

1099
01:37:27,520 --> 01:37:30,717
It was not the way he looked... Well, -

1100
01:37:30,880 --> 01:37:33,348
- at first it was the way he looked.

1101
01:37:33,520 --> 01:37:38,719
It was how he made me feel.
He made me feel romantic, -

1102
01:37:39,320 --> 01:37:42,756
- intelligent, feminine.

1103
01:37:43,880 --> 01:37:48,032
But it was not him who was
doing that to me. It was you.

1104
01:37:48,200 --> 01:37:52,318
All these other men have
flat, featureless faces.

1105
01:37:52,480 --> 01:37:57,508
No character...
No fire... No nose...

1106
01:37:57,960 --> 01:38:00,520
Charlie, you have a big nose.

1107
01:38:00,680 --> 01:38:05,390
You have a beautiful, great, big,
flesh and bone nose.

1108
01:38:05,560 --> 01:38:08,358
I love your nose.

1109
01:38:09,440 --> 01:38:12,671
I love your nose, Charlie.

1110
01:38:12,920 --> 01:38:15,480
I love you, Charlie.

1111
01:38:19,440 --> 01:38:22,716
- Well?
- Are you kidding?

1112
01:39:26,400 --> 01:39:29,472
Oh, it is locked. It is locked!

1113
01:39:30,400 --> 01:39:32,914
Thank God, I have a key.

1114
01:40:35,000 --> 01:40:40,393
- By the way, I named the comet.
- Oh yeah, good old Comet Kowalski.

1115
01:40:40,560 --> 01:40:44,872
- No, Comet Charlie.
- That is nice.

1116
01:40:45,040 --> 01:40:48,476
Yes, it is my dad's name.

1117
01:40:48,640 --> 01:40:51,438
He'll be so happy.

